description: A URL object represents a web address, like https://example.com/, and parts of the address, such as the domain, path, and query string (as URLSearchParams).
description_html: A URL object represents a web address, like https://example.com/, and parts of the address, such as the domain, path, and query string (as URLSearchParams).
name: URL

firefox.notes: Before version 57, Firefox had a bug whereby single quotes contained in URLs are escaped when accessed via URL APIs (see bug 1386683).

firefox_android.notes: Before version 57, Firefox for Android had a bug whereby single quotes contained in URLs are escaped when accessed via URL APIs (see bug 1386683).

nodejs.notes: Available as a part of the url module.

edge.notes: Before Edge 79, query arguments in the base URL argument are removed when calling the URL constructor.

firefox.notes: Before version 122, host, hostname, and port were not parsed for unknown protocols/schemes.

firefox_android.notes: Before version 122, host, hostname, and port were not parsed for unknown protocols/schemes.

safari.notes: Before Safari 14.1, calling the URL constructor with a base URL whose value is undefined caused Safari to throw a TypeError, see bug 216841.

safari_ios.notes: Before Safari on iOS 14.1, calling the URL constructor with a base URL whose value is undefined caused Safari on iOS to throw a TypeError, see bug 216841.

webview_ios.notes: Before WebView on iOS 14.1, calling the URL constructor with a base URL whose value is undefined caused WebView on iOS to throw a TypeError, see bug 216841.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 49, Results for URL using the blob scheme incorrectly returned null.

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox for Android 49, Results for URL using the blob scheme incorrectly returned null.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 53, pathname and search returned wrong values for custom protocols. Given protocol:host/x?a=true&b=false, pathname would return "/x?a=true&b=false" and search would return "", rather than "/x" and "?a=true&b=false" respectively. See bug 1310483.

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox for Android 53, pathname and search returned wrong values for custom protocols. Given protocol:host/x?a=true&b=false, pathname would return "/x?a=true&b=false" and search would return "", rather than "/x" and "?a=true&b=false" respectively. See bug 1310483.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 53, pathname and search returned wrong values for custom protocols. Given protocol:host/x?a=true&b=false, pathname would return "/x?a=true&b=false" and search would return "", rather than "/x" and "?a=true&b=false" respectively. See bug 1310483.

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox for Android 53, pathname and search returned wrong values for custom protocols. Given protocol:host/x?a=true&b=false, pathname would return "/x?a=true&b=false" and search would return "", rather than "/x" and "?a=true&b=false" respectively. See bug 1310483.

nodejs.notes: An object matching the URLSearchParams interface is returned, but it contains no data.

firefox.notes: Before version 57 single quotes in URLs were escaped (see bug 1386683).
